<br>
    1.  Mob dps.  If it can drop a pet in under 10 seconds, it may not work very well as a tactic.<br>
<br>
    2.  Mob AoE.  If it can fear, charm, or hurt a pet too quickly, it also may not work well as a tactic.<br>
<br>
    3.  Melee range to the mob.  If the mob can reach you yet you are beyond reclaim range, forget it.<br>
<br>
    4.  Aggro range and assist radius.  The lowish level of the pets might make them aggo magnets for adds, resulting in a wipeout.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
    Keeping this in mind, I would love to be one of those magicians finding out what a group of IR mags can kill....... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglisterinshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glisterin Shine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(7/8/02 10:58:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: improved reclaim, your hints/strats</span><hr size=1> to bad most mages dont know crap about the power of IR and dont wanta get it <p>
